{
  "texts": [
    "Surrogate Relevance is calculated using the inner product between Sentence-BERT embeddings of the captions.",
    "This measure is used as the training signal of the model to hone the feature embeddings generated by the GNN.",
    "The graph-to-graph comparison behind the model allows this work to better scale to large image databases when compared to [38].",
    "The use of Surrogate Relevance allows the work to be potentially expanded to match against user queries if they are in the style of the captions used to power the relevance measure.Using an image graph of K -nearest neighbour graph of images represented as feature embeddings, Liu et al. [90] propose using a GCN alongside a novel loss function based on image similarity.",
    "The feature embeddings are enhanced to account for a global context across the whole image database using a GCN."
  ]
}